## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Go 1.23+
- Docker (optional)

### Setup
1. Clone the repository
2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` (if applicable)
3. Run `go mod tidy`

### Running the App
```bash
make run
```

### Build for Production
```bash
make build
```

## Project Structure
- `cmd/server/`: Entry point of the application.
- `internal/domain/`: Core business logic and entities.
- `internal/usecase/`: Application services.
- `internal/repository/`: Data layer implementation.
- `internal/delivery/http/`: Web handlers and routes.
- `internal/infrastructure/`: Database and external service clients.

